						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">65024U wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Wait that link didn't work? I just tried it, it should, the updated files were there 0_o.....</div><br />It was timing out yesterday, but now it worked.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Yeah, at the NMI I put LDA #$00, then stored it to 2005 or some register twice for no scrolling? Wouldn't that set the equal bit to 1 so the BNE would be false and it jumps to the game loop?</div><br />No, because on interrupts the CPU flags are backed up to the stack and restored on return, so from the point of view of your waiting loop the "equal" flag will never change.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">NMI and RTI push and pull the stack, right? If so I have no variable trashing problems, right?</div>
<br />It only pushes and pulls the CPU flags. Anything else you want to use (A, X, Y) you must backup yourself.</div>

