						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">65024U wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">When my mom stops playing farmville on our Good pc</div><br />Get her a DS and Harvest Moon already <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /><br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">NMI and RTI push and pull the stack, right? If so I have no variable trashing problems, right?</div>
<br />Interrupts on 6502 push only the flags, not A, X, or Y.
<br />
<br />If you're willing to make your game loop look like this:
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">while not done:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; do stuff<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; update audio<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; prepare sprites, background updates, and palette<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; wait for vblank<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; update sprites, background updates, and palette<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; set scroll address</div>
<br />then you can use the simplest possible wait-for-vblank code seen <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/NMI#Race_condition" class="postlink">here</a>. It doesn't modify anything but the flags, so it doesn't need to push anything else.</div>

